Apr [abbreviated month]: entitlements-index-description
Apr:
Entitlements are references to functions within TeamDiagnostic. Users are granted Entitlements with Grant records. Grants inform the system that User accounts are allowed to perform special functions in the system like creating accounts, teams, and reports.
Entitlements and Grants may have quotas, tracked internally by Usages, which limit the number of times a feature can be used.

The system will automatically replace the variables with the actual values from your Facilitator profile and your Team's profile.

If you want your Title and Company Name in the closing of your letters, please manually add them.

If you want to use the Template Letters in a different language, please translate them here, but do NOT translate the variables in your letters so that they can be replaced with your actual variables.

Alternatively, you can completely replace the template letters with custom letters (without the variables) in the Cover Letter and Reminder Letter fields in the Team setup section.

Apr [abbreviated month]: template-teamdiagnostic-cover-letter
Apr:
Welcome to the Team Diagnostic
DO NOT FORWARD THIS EMAIL

Dear {{participant_name}}:

I am pleased to have the opportunity to work with you using a unique diagnostic tool developed by Team Coaching International (TCI). This tool is based on a comprehensive model of performance effectiveness that delivers a detailed map for ongoing development.

The {{assessment_name}} evaluates the entire system (also known as team or organization) rather than evaluating individuals. The key to long-term effectiveness begins with an accurate profile of strengths and challenges. The TCI approach is based on systems theory and the work of leading authorities in this emerging team development field. The model and assessment incorporate the latest work in Emotional Intelligence, Appreciative Inquiry and academic research. The resulting profile measures two axes: factors that lead to increased productivity and factors of positivity that build a stronger culture. The {{assessment_name}} profile graphically benchmarks scores in 14 separate areas.

When completing the diagnostic, please keep in mind the specific system that you are assessing.

Answer the questions from the perspective of the system as it is today, not how it was in the past or how it might be in the future. Most people complete the diagnostic in 15 to 20 minutes. Our deadline for completion is {{completion_date}}. Thank you for your cooperation.

This is your personal link to the diagnostic. Each link is individually assigned. Do not share your link or this email with anyone.

Begin Assessment
{{assessment_link}}

Please note that all diagnostic responses, including your individual written comments, will be presented anonymously as part of the overall diagnostic results. Individual responses will not be attributed to the individual that made them (i.e. your name will not appear by your written comments). We encourage you to be honest and candid to enable important issues to surface in service of improving interaction and dynamics.

If you have questions, please contact me at {{facilitator_phone}} or send email to {{facilitator_email}}. I look forward to meeting with you to review your results and plan next steps.

Sincerely,
{{facilitator_name}}


Begin Assessment
{{assessment_link}}
